The platform-specific native JARs contain a compiled WebRTC library that
statically incorporates components from the WebRTC/Chromium third_party
tree, including:

  * BoringSSL - Google's fork of OpenSSL; portions under the OpenSSL
    license, the ISC license, and others (licenses/BORINGSSL-LICENSE)
  * Abseil (abseil-cpp) - Apache License 2.0 (licenses/ABSEIL-LICENSE)
  * libyuv - 3-clause BSD license (licenses/LIBYUV-LICENSE)
  * crc32c - 3-clause BSD license (licenses/CRC32C-LICENSE)
  * libsrtp - BSD-style license, Cisco Systems (licenses/LIBSRTP-LICENSE)

The complete set of third-party notices for libwebrtc is available in the
third_party directory of the WebRTC source tree (pinned to the branch
recorded in webrtc-jni/gradle.properties) at
https://webrtc.googlesource.com/src.

In the published JARs, the license texts referenced above are located under
META-INF/licenses/; in the source repository they are in the legal/
directory.

